<h4 id="definition">Definition</h4>
<ol>
  <li>$\textbf{TRANSFORMATION OF COORDINATES}$. Let the rectangular coordinates $(x,y,z)$ of any point be expressed as functions of $u_1, u_2,u_3$ so that</li>
</ol>

<p>$
x=x\left(u_{1}, u_{2}, u_{3}\right), \quad y=y\left(u_{1}, u_{2}, u_{3}\right),
\quad z=z\left(u_{1}, u_{2}, u_{3}\right)
$</p>

<p>Given a point P with rectangluar coordinates $(x,y,z)$ we can, associate a
unique set of coordinates $(u_1,u_2,u_3)$ called curvilinear coordinates of P.</p>

